---
layout: layouts/base.njk
pagination:
  data: generated.canon.units
  size: 1
  alias: unit
permalink: "/lab/{{ unit.routeSlug }}/"
title: "Lab: {{ unit.title }}"
---
{% set labMatches = article_lab | where("unit_id", unit.id) %}
{% set lab = labMatches[0] %}
{% set claims = research_data.claims | where("article", unit.id) %}
<nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / <a href="/lab/">Article Lab</a> / {{ unit.title }}</nav>
<header class="page-head">
  <p class="eyebrow">Interpretive laboratory</p>
  <h1>{% if lab %}{{ lab.public_title }}{% else %}{{ unit.title }}{% endif %}</h1>
  <p class="lede">The body text, notes, research, failure tests, and applications remain separate layers. This is a review surface, not substitute canon and not an edcmbone metric runtime.</p>
</header>
<section>
  <h2>Conversation</h2>
  <article class="panel turn"><span class="status status-canon">Speaker A · main text</span><p>The exact canonical unit is one interaction away so this interpretive layer cannot quietly replace it.</p><p><a href="/source/{{ unit.routeSlug }}/">Open exact source and provenance</a></p></article>
  {% if unit.notes.length %}
    {% for note in unit.notes %}<article class="panel turn note"><span class="status status-interpretation">Speaker B · note {{ note.marker }}</span><p>{{ note.text }}</p></article>{% endfor %}
  {% else %}
    <article class="hmmm"><h3>No separately parsed note text</h3><p>This unit may contain no numbered annotations, or its tension may be structural rather than footnoted.</p></article>
  {% endif %}
</section>
{% if lab %}
<section>
  <p class="eyebrow">Limit testing</p>
  <h2>Reductio ad absurdum</h2>
  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card"><span class="status status-risk">Overextension</span><h3>Read without its counterweight</h3><p>{{ lab.ad_absurdum.overextension }}</p></article>
    <article class="card"><span class="status status-risk">Inverse collapse</span><h3>Reject the Article absolutely</h3><p>{{ lab.ad_absurdum.counter_overextension }}</p></article>
    <article class="card"><span class="status status-interpretation">Working boundary</span><h3>What survives both failures</h3><p>{{ lab.ad_absurdum.boundary }}</p></article>
  </div>
</section>
<section>
  <p class="eyebrow">Operational contrast</p>
  <h2>Worst practices and best practices</h2>
  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card"><span class="status status-risk">Worst practices</span><h3>How the Article becomes harmful</h3><ul>{% for practice in lab.worst_practices %}<li>{{ practice }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul></article>
    <article class="card"><span class="status status-implemented">Best practices</span><h3>How the tension becomes usable</h3><ul>{% for practice in lab.best_practices %}<li>{{ practice }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul></article>
  </div>
</section>
<section>
  <p class="eyebrow">Contact across kinds of work</p>
  <h2>Applications by domain</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">These are bounded application hypotheses. A domain must preserve its own standards, evidence, lawful duties, and safety constraints rather than importing the Article as a slogan.</p>
  <div class="grid">
    {% for domain, application in lab.applications %}<article class="card"><span class="status status-public">{{ domain }}</span><p>{{ application }}</p></article>{% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
<section>
  <p class="eyebrow">Reviewed contact</p>
  <h2>Research field</h2>
  {% if claims.length %}
    <div class="grid">
      {% for claim in claims %}
        {% set stanceClass = "status-research" %}
        {% if claim.stance == "dissent" %}{% set stanceClass = "status-risk" %}{% endif %}
        {% if claim.stance == "limit" or claim.stance == "mixed" %}{% set stanceClass = "status-frontier" %}{% endif %}
        <article class="card">
          <span class="status {{ stanceClass }}">{{ claim.stance }} · {{ claim.status }}</span>
          <h3>{{ claim.claim }}</h3>
          <p><strong>Evidence boundary:</strong> {{ claim.limitation }}</p>
          <div class="source-list"><strong>Sources:</strong><ul>
            {% for sourceId in claim.source_ids %}
              {% for source in research_data.sources %}
                {% if source.id == sourceId %}<li><a href="{{ source.url }}">{{ source.title }}</a><br><small>{{ source.type }} · reviewed {{ source.reviewed_on }}</small></li>{% endif %}
              {% endfor %}
            {% endfor %}
          </ul></div>
        </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  {% else %}
    <div class="hmmm"><p>No reviewed claim is attached to this unit yet.</p></div>
  {% endif %}
</section>
{% else %}
<section><h2>What the tension prevents</h2><div class="hmmm"><p>A reviewed synthesis, absurd-limit test, practice contrast, and domain application set have not yet been admitted for this non-Rights unit.</p></div></section>
<section><h2>Research field</h2><div class="hmmm"><p>No reviewed source is attached to this unit yet.</p></div></section>
{% endif %}
<details><summary>Open EDCM-style heuristic boundary</summary><p>This page may later expose transparent text-comparison heuristics such as constraint mismatch, drift, dissonance, divergence, and turn balance. Those readings must remain labeled illustrative and may not claim edcmbone runtime status.</p></details>
